==Old English==
===Etymology===
Etymology uncertain.  Cognate with Old Frisian [[hengst]], Old High German [[hengist]] (German [[Hengst]] ‘stallion’), Middle Low German [[hingst]] (Dutch [[hengst]]), Old Norse [[hestr]] (Swedish [[häst]]).

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'heŋgest/

===Noun===
'''hengest''' ''m''
# [[horse]], [[gelding]], [[stallion]]
#:''An hundred wildra horsa and xvi tame hencgestas'': a hundred wild horses and sixteen tame stallions.  (''Diplomatarium Anglicum'')

